2025-12-12 | Maximum Square Inside Intersection of Rectangles

	Question
Given arrays bottomLeft and topRight describing rectangles,  
return the maximum area of a square that can fit inside the intersection of at least two rectangles.

	Approach
1.	Key observation:
	-	The intersection of two rectangles is also an axis-aligned rectangle.
	-	If that intersection has width w and height h,
	  the largest square that fits inside it has side:
			side = min(w, h)
2.	Brute-force over all **pairs of rectangles**:
	-	Since the requirement is “at least two rectangles”, checking all pairs is sufficient.
3.	For each pair (i, j):
	1.	Compute intersection rectangle:
		-	left   = max(aᵢ, aⱼ)
		-	right  = min(cᵢ, cⱼ)
		-	bottom = max(bᵢ, bⱼ)
		-	top    = min(dᵢ, dⱼ)
	2.	If right > left and top > bottom:
		-	Intersection exists with positive area.
	3.	Compute:
			width  = right − left
			height = top − bottom
			side   = min(width, height)
			area   = side × side
	4.	Update the maximum area.
4.	If no valid intersection produces a positive square, return 0.
5.	Time Complexity:
	-	O(n²), checking all rectangle pairs.
6.	Space Complexity:
	-	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    long long maxSquareArea(vector<vector<int>>& bottomLeft,
                            vector<vector<int>>& topRight) {
        int n = bottomLeft.size();
        long long ans = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                // Intersection boundaries
                int left   = max(bottomLeft[i][0], bottomLeft[j][0]);
                int right  = min(topRight[i][0],  topRight[j][0]);
                int bottom = max(bottomLeft[i][1], bottomLeft[j][1]);
                int top    = min(topRight[i][1],  topRight[j][1]);

                // Check if intersection exists
                if (right > left && top > bottom) {
                    long long width  = right - left;
                    long long height = top - bottom;
                    long long side = min(width, height);
                    ans = max(ans, side * side);
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
